body_html: Most bicubic interpolants are not guaranteed to be monotonic, since the cubic interpolant's extrema can exceed the original extrema in the given interval. Just clamp your image to allowable value after running the resize_cubic call. i.e. 0, 255 or 0, 1 depending on float or int types.

body: Most bicubic interpolants are not guaranteed to be monotonic, since the cubic interpolant's extrema can exceed the original extrema in the given interval. Just clamp your image to allowable value after running the resize_cubic call. i.e. 0, 255 or 0, 1 depending on float or int types.
